    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-05-04T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-05-04T12:00:00-05:00" n="1200"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1200">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/34041: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-05-04T13:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 4, 1944—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1550. For Tittmann. Your 131, April 13—Bern’s 2580, April 22. With the
                    concurrence of the War Department you may in your discretion acknowledge the
                    Vatican’s memorandum of April 12 repeating that the Allied Commanders in the
                    field have unquestionable evidence that the Abbey of Monte Cassino formed part
                    of the German defensive system.<note n="35" xml:id="d1200fn1">For a discussion
                        of this subject, see Martin Blumenson, <hi rend="italic">Salerno to
                            Cassino</hi>, in the official Army history <hi rend="italic">United
                            States Army in World War II</hi> (in preparation).</note> We have no
                    further comments to make at this time.</p>
                <p>Sent to Bern, repeated to Algiers.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
